  "chapter": {
    "number": 30,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Job’s Honor Turned to Contempt"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“But now they mock me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "men younger than I am,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "whose fathers I would have refused",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to entrust with my sheep dogs.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What use to me was the strength of their hands,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "since their vigor had left them?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Gaunt from poverty and hunger,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they gnawed the dry land,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the desolate wasteland by night.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They plucked mallow among the shrubs,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the roots of the broom tree were their food.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3188
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They were banished from among men,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "shouted down like thieves,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "so that they lived on the slopes of the wadis,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "among the rocks and in holes in the ground.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They cried out among the shrubs",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and huddled beneath the nettles.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A senseless and nameless brood,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they were driven off the land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And now they mock me in song;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have become a byword among them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They abhor me and keep far from me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they do not hesitate to spit in my face.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Because God has unstrung my bow and afflicted me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they have cast off restraint",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3189
          },
          {
            "text": "in my presence.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The rabble arises at my right;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they lay snares for my feet",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and build siege ramps against me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They tear up my path;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they profit from my destruction,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "with no one to restrain them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3190
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They advance as through a wide breach;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "through the ruins they keep rolling in.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Job’s Prosperity Becomes Calamity"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Terrors are turned loose against me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they drive away my dignity as by the wind,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and my prosperity has passed like a cloud.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And now my soul is poured out within me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "days of affliction grip me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Night pierces my bones,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my gnawing pains never rest.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "With great force He grasps my garment;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3191
          },
          {
            "text": "He seizes me by the collar of my tunic.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He throws me into the mud,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I have become like dust and ashes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I cry out to You for help, but You do not answer;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when I stand up, You merely look at me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have ruthlessly turned on me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You oppose me with Your strong hand.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You snatch me up into the wind",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and drive me before it;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You toss me about",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3192
          },
          {
            "text": "in the storm.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yes, I know that You will bring me down to death,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the place appointed for all the living.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet no one stretches out his hand to a ruined man",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when he cries for help in his distress.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Have I not wept for those in trouble?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Has my soul not grieved for the needy?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But when I hoped for good, evil came;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when I looked for light, darkness fell.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I am churning within and cannot rest;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "days of affliction confront me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I go about blackened, but not by the sun.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I stand up in the assembly and cry for help.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I have become a brother of jackals,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3193
          },
          {
            "text": "a companion of ostriches.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3194
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My skin grows black and peels,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my bones burn with fever.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My harp is tuned to mourning",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my flute to the sound of weeping.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
